# ðš« now API [![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/timolins/now-api.svg)](https://travis-ci.org/timolins/now-api)

Node.js module to interact with the official [ðš« now API](https://zeit.co/api). You need to provide your API token, which you can find in `~/.now.json`.

```sh
npm install --save now-api
```

## Example
```js
var Now = require('now-api');

var now = Now('YOUR TOKEN');

// Supports Promises
now.getDeployments().then((deployments) => {
    console.log(deployments);
}).catch((err) => {
    console.error(err);
});

// Or go old-school with callbacks
now.getDeployments(function(err, deployments) {
    if (err) throw err;
    console.log(deployments);
});
```

